A Muleshoe, Texas tradition on Halloween is for costumed young people ride in 50 gallon drums painted like cows in a train pulled around in the downtown. 

In rural areas farms are too far apart to trick or treat, so families drive to the business district for a âTrunk or Treatâ and open up the back of their cars to hand out candy.
